IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: On Tuesday, October 31st, 2023 at approximately 1745, myself and Cpl. Wynne #6594, Anne Arundel County Police, and EMS responded to eastbound I-695 at Ritchie Hwy. for a reported shooting with one victim sustaining a gunshot wound to the leg. Anne Arundel County Officer Spates # 2442 was one of the first responders on scene and observed the victim, later identified as James Richard Rhodes 9/11/00, with a gunshot wound high on his left leg. Officer Spates applied pressure on the wound until EMS arrived on scene.Cpl. Wynne arrived on scene. Rhodes was transported to R Adams Cowley Shock Trauma Center,22 S Greene St, Baltimore, MD 21201, via Medic # 32 run # 202379961. I arrived on the scene afterRhodes was transported to the hospital. I observed a red Subaru Impreza hatchback bearing Maryland registration 5FP1395 on the left shoulder of I-695. I observed one bullet hole in the drivers door and the window of the drivers door was shattered. After speaking with Cpl. Wynne and Officer Spates,Rhodes was allegedly involved in a road rage incident with another vehicle described as a red Dodge Grand Caravan bearing Maryland registration 9FD1470. The driver of the Dodge allegedly shot atRhodes, to which the bullet traveled through the drivers door and struckRhodes left leg while driving. Officer Spates was provided with the suspects tag and vehicle description and was able to showRhodes a picture of the registered owner, whoRhodes positively identified as the suspect. The suspect was identified as the registered owner of the Dodge, Keith Bryant Felton Jr. 3/25/99. Rhodes was not certain of the exact place the shooting occurred and had driven a short distance until he pulled over on the left shoulder of I-695 at Ritchie Hwy. An Anne Arundel County Police helicopter was airborne and was searching the area for the suspect vehicle. The helicopter flew over the suspects listed address of 6315 Seton Ridge Dr. in Gwynn Oak, Maryland searching for the vehicle. The suspect vehicle was not located at the residence at that time. Maryland State Police Criminal Enforcement Division was notified. Cpl. Wynne responded to shock trauma to stay withRhodes. I remained on scene withRhodes vehicle.Rhodes vehicle was towed to the Maryland State Police Glen Burnie Barrack by White Huff Towing for further investigation. The vehicle was secured in the barrack vehicle storage lot at 1820 hrs. At 1940 hrs, Scott Brice Evans 3/7/1990, (443) 904-7361, called the Maryland State Police Glen Burnie Barrack stating he witnessed the shooting on I-695. Evans stated he observed the red Subaru and red Dodge both engaged in a road rage situation, cutting each other off, etc. eastbound on I-695 in the area of Route 1. Evans stated the aggressive driving continued in the area of I-97 where he saw the driver of the Subaru holding his cell phone up to the window and heard possibly 3 gun shots come from the Dodge. Evans stated after the shooting, the Dodge continued on southbound I-97 at a high rate of speed. Evans information was provided to S/Tpr Costello #5827 assigned to the Criminal Enforcement Division to follow up. All events occurred in Anne Arundel County, Maryland. I request this case remain open and forwarded to Criminal Enforcement Division and Crime Scene for further investigation.

IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeTitle: CED: Initial Case Review, Response to Hospital, Victim Interview
IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: CASE REPORT:23-MSP-038407 INVESTIGATOR:Senior Trooper W. Costello #5827 UNIT:Criminal Enforcement Division (CED) DATE ASSIGNED:October 31, 2023 CASE STATUS: Closed by arrest FOCUS: CED Initial Case Review, Response to Hospital, Victim Interview SCENE PROCESSING: 1) Maryland State Police Crime Scene was requested and responded to the scene to process the victims vehicle as evidence. 2) License Plate Recognition System (LPR) records were requested in the area of this incident. 3) The Maryland Gun Center was contacted. The Gun Center completed a case report for Felton (Case #202308052). A copy of this report was obtained and is attached to this report. 4) Investigators checked the area for video surveillance cameras. 5) Maryland Coordination Analysis Center (MCAC) was contacted and provided further LPR records assistance. 6) Body cameras from allied agencys were requested related to this case. 7) Recorded interviews with the victim was completed. 8) Consent was obtained from the victim to search his vehicle and cellular phone. 9) Investigators responded to the area of the shooting to inspect for casings and other evidence yielding negative results. 10) The victims phone was analyzed by a Digital Forensic examiner. PHYSICAL EVIDENCE: Evidence Recovered on scene at the Hospital: 1) One (1) metal bullet projectile, surgically recovered by the Hospital Staff from inside the Victim. 2) One (1) hospital bag containing the victims blood-soaked clothing. 3) One (1) Apple iPhone red in color, cellular telephone with black case. 4) Photographs of the suspect vehicle were obtained from the victim. Evidence Recovered by Crime Scene: Victims Vehicle: 1) One (1) Projectile jacket from drivers side under the drivers door/seat track. Vehicle: 1) One (1) vehicle was seized and towed from the scene to the Maryland State Police Glenn Bernie Barrack to be processed as evidence. Vehicle make / model: Subaru / Impreza Vehicle year: 2024 Vehicle color: Red Maryland registration: 5FP1395 Vehicle Identification Number (VIN): JF1GUAFC1R8282017 Digital Evidence: 1) One (1) Cellebrite phone download of victims iPhone. NARRATIVE: On October 31, 2023, at approximately 1634 hours, Troopers with the Maryland State Police Glen Burnie barrack were dispatched to the area of eastbound I-695 at Exit 3 for a reported shooting with one victim sustaining a gunshot wound to the leg. Anne Arundel County Officer Spates # 2442 was one of the first responders on scene and observed the victim with a gunshot wound high on his left leg. Officer Spates applied pressure on the wound until EMS arrived on scene.Cpl. Wynne and TFC Wahl with the Maryland State Police, arrived on scene and the victim was transported to R Adams Cowley Shock Trauma Center,22 S Greene St, Baltimore, MD 21201, via Medic # 32 run # 202379961.The victim, was identified as, James Richard Rhodes, U/M, 09/11/2000. The Troopers observed a red Subaru Impreza bearing Maryland registration 5FP1395 on the left shoulder of I-695 and observed one bullet hole in the drivers door and the window of the drivers door was shattered. Cpl. Wynne advised the victim was engaged in a road rage incident with another vehicle described as a red Dodge Grand Caravan bearing Maryland registration 9FD1470. The driver of the Dodge allegedly shot at Rhodes causing his injury.Rhodes stated he observed the suspect was a black male, in his 20s, approximately 509, short black facial hair and a red hat. The registered owner of the maroon Dodge van was identified as Keith Bryant Felton, B/M, 03/25/1999 who matched the description given by Rhodes. An MVA photograph of Felton was shown to Rhodes on scene and he positively confirmed that Felton was the suspect who fired a handgun at him on I-695. Rhodes advised he was not certain of the exact location the shooting occurred and had driven a short distance until he pulled over on the left shoulder of I-695 at Ritchie Hwy. An Anne Arundel County Police helicopter responded and searched the area for the suspect vehicle yielding negative results. Cpl. Wynne responded to shock trauma to stay withRhodes and made contact with the investigators with Criminal Enforcement Division (CED) Central/South. Rhodes vehicle was towed to the Maryland State Police Glen Burnie Barrack by White Huff Towing for further investigation. The vehicle was secured in the barrack vehicle storage lot at 1820 hrs. At 1940 hrs, Scott Brice Evans 3/7/1990, (443) 904-7361, called the Maryland State Police Glen Burnie Barrack stating he witnessed the shooting on I-695. Evans stated he observed the red Subaru and red Dodge both engaged in a road rage situation, cutting each other off, etc. eastbound on I-695 in the area of Route 1. Evans stated the aggressive driving continued in the area of I-97 where he saw the driver of the Subaru holding his cell phone up to the window and heard possibly 3 gun shots come from the Dodge. Evans stated after the shooting, the dodge continued on southbound I-97 at a high rate of speed. Evans information was provided to S/Tpr Costello #5827 assigned to the Criminal Enforcement Division to follow up. ST Costello and Cpl Posey with CED responded to the hospital and spoke with Cpl Wynne about the incident. At that time, ST Costello assumed the investigation and a recorded interview was conducted at the hospital with Rhodes. Rhodes advised he was operating his red Subaru Impreza displaying Maryland registration 5FP1395 on I-695 when he observed the suspect vehicle, a maroon Dodge Grand Caravan displaying Maryland registration 9FD1470. Rhodes advised the Dodge cut him off and he got angry so he drove around the Dodge and cut him off which caused the driver of the Dodge to become agitated and start yelling at him out of the window. Rhodes advised they were in congested traffic on 695 and occasionally would stop in traffic. Rhodes advised the suspect was yelling at him out the window asking him to pull over and fight and Rhodes advised he was yelling back at him. Rhodes advised he did pull onto the shoulder and the suspect vehicle pulled in behind him and the suspect stepped partially out of the vehicle (one foot in one foot out of the vehicle) but then got back in his car and kept driving. Rhodes advised he was on I-695 at I-97 in Anne Arundel County, when the maroon Dodge pulled into the shoulder adjacent to him and rolled his passenger side window down. Rhodes advised there was a short concrete jersey wall between them when he heard a single pop sound and his drivers side window was broken by gunfire. Rhodes advised he immediately took out his cell phone camera and took a photo of the suspects vehicle and his registration. Rhodes provided the photo to investigators and confirmed the vehicle and registration. Rhodes advised he observed the suspect was holding a black handgun and fire 2 additional rounds at his vehicle, one of which struck him in the left upper thigh. The following items were recovered as evidence from the victim and scene: Evidence Recovered on scene at the Hospital: 1) One (1) metal bullet projectile, surgically recovered by the Hospital Staff from inside the Victim. 2) One (1) hospital bag containing the victims blood-soaked clothing. 3) One (1) Apple iPhone red in color, cellular telephone with black case. 4) One (1) vehicle was seized and towed from the scene to the Maryland State Police Glenn Bernie Barrack to be processed as evidence. Vehicle make / model: Subaru / Impreza Vehicle year: 2024 Vehicle color: Red Maryland registration: 5FP1395 Vehicle Identification Number (VIN): JF1GUAFC1R8282017 Evidence Recovered by Crime Scene: Victims Vehicle: 1) One (1) Projectile jacket from drivers side under the drivers door/seat track. The victims phone was analyzed by a digital forensic examiner and a copy was downloaded using Cellebrite. A copy of the phone was created and stored as evidence and the phone was released back to the victim.

SCENE PROCESSING: 1) A search warrant application was completed 2) Maryland STATE Team was requested to assist 3) Suspect was read his Advised of Miranda rights and completed an MSP form 180. 4) A recorded interview was conducted with the suspect 5) Photographs were taken of the residence during the search warrant. PHYSICAL EVIDENCE: Firearms/Ammunition: PH- 345620 1) Item A1: One (1) MasterPiece Arms MPA defender 9mm handgun with silencer. SN:FX42195 2) Item B1: One (1) MasterPiece Arms extended magazine. 3) Item C1: Eleven (11) live rounds of 9mm ammunition. 4) Item A2: One (1) Smith and Wesson MP shield .45 caliber handgun. SN:62-H21YD-000700 11) Item A5: One (1) Vigilant Tactical VR-15 rifle. SN:01036 Ammunition: PH- 345621 1) Item A: Fifty (50) live rounds of Fiocchi 9mm ammunition 2) Item B: One (1) magazine containing Six (6) live rounds of .40 caliber ammunition and Three (3) loose rounds of .40 caliber ammunition 3) Item C: Four (4) loose rounds of .45 caliber ammunition 4) Item D: Two (2) boxes of live rounds of .45 caliber ammunition, forty eight (48) total rounds of ammunition. Electronic Equipment: 1) One (1) iPhone, white in color, cellular telephone with black phone case, unknown serial number belonging to suspect: Keith Felton. Other Evidence: 1) One (1) Uncle Mikes firearm holster. Recovered from inside the suspects vehicle 2) One (1) multicolored beanie style hat NARRATIVE: Investigators responded to Feltons registered home address, 6315 Seton Ridge Dr, Gwynn Oak, MD and observed the maroon Dodge Grand Caravan displaying Maryland registration 9FD1470 parked at that residence. Investigators completed a search and seizure warrant for Feltons registered home address, 6315 Seton Ridge Dr, Gwynn Oak, MD. The Maryland State Police STATE Team responded and made entry to the residence. A search was conducted resulting in the seizure of Feltons cell phone and multiple firearms. Felton was interviewed on scene and advised he wanted to make a limited statement about the incident. Felton advised he saw the victims vehicle and described it as a red car. Felton advised the victim flashed him and explained that means he flashed a gun at him. Felton advised the victim tried to block him in and he was trying to drive away from him. Felton was asked more about the incident at which time he advised he wanted to obtain the assistance of an attorney. At that time no further questions were asked and the interview was completed. While being served the search warrant copy, the suspects mother stated Felton contacted her on the phone and spoke about the incident, advising that the narrative on the warrant did not match the story Felton gave her. Based on the above information Felton was placed under arrest and charged with the following: 1) 2 0910 Att Murder, CR 2-206 2) 1 1420, ASSAULT-FIRST DEGREE, CR 3-202 3) 1 1425, RECKLESS ENDANGERMENT, CR 3-204(a)(1) 4) 1 1430, RECK ENDANGERMENT FROM CAR, CR 3-204(a)(2) 5) 5 299, Firearm - use/fel viol crime, CR 4-204 The following evidence was recovered during the residential search warrant: Firearms/Ammunition: PH- 345620 1) Item A1: One (1) MasterPiece Arms MPA defender 9mm handgun with silencer. IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeTitle: CED: Witness Attempted Interview Shatoyia Taylor
IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: CASE REPORT:23-MSP-038407 INVESTIGATOR:Senior Trooper W. Costello #5827 UNIT:Criminal Enforcement Division (CED) DATE ASSIGNED:October 31, 2023 CASE STATUS: Closed by arrest FOCUS: CED: Witness Attempted Interview with Shatoyia Taylor NARRATIVE: Investigators contacted Taylor multiple times attempting to interview her about the incident. Taylor agreed to respond to the barracks. Investigators waited for Taylor who then failed to respond on two occasions. Investigators made several additional attempts to contact her by telephone yielding negative results. Taylor was unable to be contacted for interview and was uncooperative.

CASE REPORT:23-MSP-038407 INVESTIGATOR:Senior Trooper W. Costello #5827 UNIT:Criminal Enforcement Division (CED) DATE ASSIGNED:October 31, 2023 CASE STATUS: Closed by arrest FOCUS: CED: Witness Interview Joshua Pfeiffer WITNESS INTERVIEWED: Joshua Daniel Pfeiffer W/M, DOB: 10/21/1979 16 Oakmont Ct, Denver PA Cell: 717-538-4418 PA Soundex: 25042312 NARRATIVE: On November 6, 2023, at approximately 1510 hours investigators made contact with a witness identified as Joshua Daniel Pfeiffer, W/M, DOB: 10/21/1979.Pfeiffer advised he was traveling in the opposite direction of the two vehicles, he described as a red Subaru and a Maroon Dodge Caravan.Pfeiffer advised he works with the County Emergency services and was driving his marked AA County emergency vehicle when he observed the two vehicles driving aggressively, and it caught his eye.Pfeiffer advised they were in stop and go traffic, and he observed the Subaru and Dodge passing each other using lane 1 and the shoulder. Pfeiffer advised he observed the Subaru pulled out of the way of the Dodge onto the shoulder and the Dodge pulled up next to the Subaru.Pfeiffer advised he observed the driver of the Dodge had his drivers side window rolled down and was yelling at the Subaru driver as he drove next to him, but could not hear what was said.Pfeiffer described the driver of the Dodge to be a black male wearing sunglasses, and the driver of the Subaru to also be a black male, but he did not see him as well.Pfeiffer advised he passed the vehicles and watched them in his rear-view mirror continue to drive in front of each other, but he did not see anything related to a shooting.Pfeiffer advised it was hard to tell who was the aggressor in the road rage incident, they appeared to both be driving erratically but he advised the driver of the Dodge was the only one he observed yelling out of the window. This interview was audibly and visually recorded on ST Costellos Axon Body Worn Camera #0016715.

CASE REPORT:23-MSP-038407 INVESTIGATOR:Senior Trooper W. Costello #5827 UNIT:Criminal Enforcement Division (CED) DATE ASSIGNED:October 31, 2023 CASE STATUS: Closed by arrest FOCUS: CED: Witness Interview Scott Evans WITNESS INTERVIEWED: Scott Brice Evans W/M, DOB: 03/07/1990 415 Phirne Rd West, Glen Burnie MD Cell:443-904-7361 MD Soundex: E152760098174 NARRATIVE: On November 6, 2023, at approximately 1700 hours, investigators made contact with a witness identified as Scott Brice Evans W/M, DOB: 03/07/1990.Evans advised he was traveling on I-695 in his blue Camaro, reg 5AZ4654 in lane 2 when he observed the red Subaru approaching his vehicle from the rear at what he advised was a high speed and then enter lane 1 passing him. Evans advised the traffic was stopped, and he ended up passing the red Subaru, and he noticed the Dodge Caravan and the red Subaru start passing each other and driving erratically. Evans advised he ended up behind the Dodge and watched the two vehicles passing each other and swerving back and forth for a few exits. Evans advised he observed the driver of the Subaru quickly exit as if he was trying to get away from the Dodge and then the Dodge slowed and began driving slow and swerving. Evans said he suspected the Dodge was swerving like he was not paying attention to the road and was trying to grab something in the vehicle. Evans advised he observed the red Subaru on the other side of a concrete barrier, and he was filming the Dodge with his phone when he heard the Dodge fire a shot.Evans advised there was a short delay, and then he heard another shot and was uncertain if it was a total of 2 or 3 shots.Evans advised the Dodge continued on 97 south and around the Quarterfield Road exit the Dodge accelerated to a high rate of speed (estimated at 100 plus MPH) and took off. Evans advised he could not determine who was more aggressive during the road rage and advised they were both driving aggressively until the shot from the Dodge.This interview was audibly and visually recorded on ST Costellos Axon Body Worn Camera #0016715.

IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeTitle: CED: Recovered USB drive containing video from ST John's Dash-cam
IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: CASE REPORT:23-MSP-038407 INVESTIGATOR:Senior Trooper W. Costello #5827 UNIT:Criminal Enforcement Division (CED) DATE ASSIGNED:October 31, 2023 CASE STATUS: Closed by arrest FOCUS: CED recovered dash camera footage from witness at ST John Digital Evidence: 1) One (1) USB drive containing video from ST Johns Dash-cam NARRATIVE: On November 14, 2023, investigators recovered a USB drive containing video surveillance of the incident that was recovered from an Saint Johns Property vehicles dashcam. The videos were uploaded to the case file and the USB was stored as evidence.

Incident Date: October 31 and November 1, 2023 Incident: Transport of Keith Felton and other assist actions Attachments: 1) Body Worn Camera footage from search warrant and transport of prisoner 2) Arrest photos of Keith Felton taken at Glen Burnie Barrack Narrative: On October 31, 2023 I became aware of a first degree assault investigation being conducted by members of the MSP Glen Burnie Barrack and Southern Region Criminal Enforcement Division. I responded to assist with a search warrant being conducted at6315 Seton Ridge Dr, Gwynn Oak, MD. While executing the search warrant, the identified suspect Keith Felton was taken into custody. Felton was placed into my agency issued vehicle at approximately 0444 hours and I transported him to Glen Burnie Barrack. My agency issued BWC was activated the entire time and the footage has been uploaded to evidence.com. Upon arrival at the Glen Burnie Barrack I also took three photos of Felton which were also documented on evidence.com and are further attached to this report. Felton appeared healthy the entire time I was with him and never exhibited any physical issues. For further details regarding this investigation, refer to supplements by S/T Costello. Case closed.
